text: Robert Largan (born 29 May 1987) is a British politician who was the Member of Parliament (MP) for High Peak from 2019 to 2024. He served as Assistant Government Whip from October 2022 until July 2024. At the 2019 general election, Largan was elected as the Member of Parliament for High Peak with a majority of 590 and with 45.9% of the vote. He was beaten by Labour candidate Jon Pearce in the 2024 general election. ==References== Category:UK MPs 2019â€“2024 Category:1987 births Category:Living people
